In this statement, the President expresses his observance of Holocaust Remembrance Day and honors the memories of the six million Jewish victims and others who perished in the Holocaust. He also pays tribute to those who resisted the Nazis and those who survived. The President reaffirms the collective responsibility to confront anti-Semitism, prejudice, and intolerance, as he had the opportunity to visit Yad Vashem, Israel's national Holocaust memorial during his recent trip to Israel. On this Yom Hashoah, the President emphasizes the importance of remembrance and committing ourselves to understanding, empathy, and compassion as the foundation of peace and human dignity.